SECTION 1.
(a) By July 1, 2025, the speakers shall appoint a study committee to plan for the
building of an appropriate facility in the western grand division of Tennessee to house
children who are being detained, pursuant to ยง 37-1-114, while awaiting adjudication on
allegations of delinquency or unruliness.
(b) The study committee shall be composed of:
(1) The following members to be appointed by the speaker of the house
of representatives:
(A) A sheriff from a county in the western grand division;
(B) A judge from a county in the western grand division; and
(C) Two (2) members of the house of representatives; and
(2) The following members to be appointed by the speaker of the senate:
(A) A sheriff from a county in the western grand division;
(B) A judge from a county in the western grand division; and
(C) Two (2) members of the senate.
(c) The members of the study committee shall receive no compensation for their
service on the committee, nor are the members entitled to per diem or travel expenses
for the purposes of carrying out their duties under this section.
(d) The study committee shall determine and make recommendations for the
location of the facility, the number of beds to be included, and the entity that should
